Bug 1877420 - Fix compose window not opening for file arguments without recognized extension. r=arschmitz

The patch for Bug 1800423 changed OpenComposeWindow and
OpenComposeWindowWithParams to pass `win` (a DOM Window) as the first
argument instead of `null`. These APIs expect `msgComposeWindowURL`
(a string URL or null), so the Window coerced to "[object Window]"
is not a valid chrome URL, causing both calls to fail.

In the file-as-attachment fallback, the caught error falls through
to openURI(), which triggers the external helper app dialog without
a window context, resulting in a console error instead of opening
the compose window.

The X-Unsent .eml case (OpenComposeWindow) was also affected but
happened to work because the C++ implementation takes an early return
via LoadDraftOrTemplate() for compose type Draft, which never uses
the msgComposeWindowURL parameter.

Restore `null` in both call sites for correctness.

Differential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D310578


